<subSubSection id="C18265170723FF8CF7E9FA4362EB413B" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8927369C0723FF8CF7E9FA4363914027" blockId="15.[2072,2669,1466,1888]" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis id="BBECEA8E0723FF8CF7E9FA4363BA43D5" bold="true" box="[2074,2229,1466,1495]" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F0723FF8CF726FA43635143FD" authority="Bangs, 1902" authorityName="Bangs" authorityYear="1902" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cavator">Macrogeomys cavator Bangs, 1902</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="39F03CC10723FF8CF78DFA1F63914027" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3799834312" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">“Boquete, 4,800 feet” (Chiriqui, Panama).</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8927369C0723FF8CF7E9F9C962EB413B" blockId="15.[2072,2669,1466,1888]" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F0723FF8CF697F9C96104404F" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[2404,2571,1584,1613]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Macrogeomys</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F0723FF8CF5D1F9C963724076" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">Heterogeomys</taxonomicName>
considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F0723FF8CF604F9AA6346409E" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">Orthogeomys</taxonomicName>
by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genus status by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that H. cavatoris sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F0723FF8CF61BF9086336413B" authorityName="Goldman" authorityYear="1912" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dariensis">H. dariensis</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C18265170723FF8CF7EBF8C663DB41D6" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" type="synonymic_list">
<caption id="DDE766140723FF8CF7EBF8C663DB41D6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6603871" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6603871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6603871/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" targetBox="[1459,2049,1466,1879]" targetPageId="15">
